  "prompt": "How can we find people on WhatsApp without their phone number?",
  "response": "Finding people on WhatsApp without their phone number can be challenging, as the app primarily relies on phone numbers for contact. However, here are a few potential methods:\n\n1. Mutual Contacts\n- If you have mutual contacts who have the person saved in their phone, they might appear in your contact suggestions.\n\n2. WhatsApp QR Code\n- You can scan someone's WhatsApp QR code if you're physically near them.\n\n3. WhatsApp Web/Desktop\n- If the person is already in a group chat you're part of, you might be able to find their profile.\n\n4. Social Media Cross-Referencing\n- Check if they've linked their WhatsApp to other social media platforms.\n\n5. WhatsApp Business Profile\n- Some businesses have public WhatsApp business profiles.\n\n6. WhatsApp Link\n- Some people share their WhatsApp link on social media profiles.\n\n7. Third-Party Apps (Caution Advised)\n- Some apps claim to help find WhatsApp contacts, but many are unreliable or potentially unsafe.\n\nImportant Considerations:\n- WhatsApp prioritizes privacy\n- Most methods require some existing connection\n- Always respect people's privacy\n- Be cautious of third-party apps that might compromise personal data\n\nThe most reliable way to connect remains having their actual phone number.",
